---
// Components
// - Layout
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
// - UI
import SidebarContent from '../components/blocks/basic/StickySidebar.astro'
import Hero from '../components/blocks/hero/PageHeader.astro'

// Content
// - SEO
const SEO = {
	title: 'KLOOW | Terms of Service',
	description:
		"KLOOW's Terms of Service outline the rules and guidelines for using our SaaS tools. Please review them to understand your rights and responsibilities."
}

// - Page Header
const header = {
	title: 'Terms and Conditions: Clear, Simple, <strong>Trusted</strong>',
	text: 'Please review these terms to understand your rights and responsibilities while using KLOOW.'
}
---

<Layout title={SEO.title} description={SEO.description}>
	<Hero title={header.title} text={header.text} />
	<SidebarContent>
		<div slot="sidebar">
			<h3>Introduction</h3>
			<p>
				Please take a moment to read through these terms to understand your rights and
				responsibilities while using our services.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="basic-text">
			<h4>Welcome to KLOOW</h4>
			<p>
				We’re excited to have you on board. KLOOW provides powerful SaaS tools to simplify
				and automate digital marketing for startups, brands, and agencies. By using our
				platform, you agree to these Terms of Service, so please take a moment to read them
				carefully.
			</p>
			<p>
				Your success matters to us. If you have any questions about these terms, our team is
				here to help and ensure you get the most out of KLOOW.
			</p>

			<h4>Acceptance of Terms</h4>
			<p>
				By accessing or using our services, you agree to comply with and be bound by these
				Terms of Service and our Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with any part of these
				terms, you should not use our services. Continued use of KLOOW confirms your
				acceptance of these terms.
			</p>
			<p>
				We may update these terms from time to time. Any changes will be posted on our
				website, and it is your responsibility to review them periodically. Ongoing use of
				our services after updates means you accept the revised terms.
			</p>

			<h4>Our Commitment to You</h4>
			<p>
				At KLOOW, we are committed to providing innovative, reliable, and high-quality tools
				that help you streamline marketing workflows, enhance productivity, and grow your
				business. We continually work to improve our platform so you always have the best
				possible experience.
			</p>
			<p>
				We welcome your feedback and ideas. Share your thoughts with us, and together we’ll
				make KLOOW even better at helping you achieve your marketing goals.
			</p>
		</div>
	</SidebarContent>
	<SidebarContent classes="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-900">
		<div slot="sidebar">
			<h3>User Accounts</h3>
			<p></p>
		</div>
		<div class="basic-text">
			<h4>Registration</h4>
			<p>
				To access certain features of KLOOW, you must create a user account. By registering,
				you agree to provide accurate and complete information. This helps us deliver the
				best experience while maintaining the security and reliability of your account.
			</p>
			<p>
				You also agree to keep your information up to date. Outdated or inaccurate details
				may cause issues with your account and limit access to certain features of KLOOW.
			</p>

			<h4>Account Security</h4>
			<p>
				You are responsible for keeping your account secure. Your password must remain
				confidential, and you should never share it with others. If you notice any
				unauthorized activity, please notify us immediately.
			</p>
			<p>
				We recommend creating a strong, unique password and updating it regularly. If
				two-factor authentication is available, we encourage you to enable it for added
				protection.
			</p>

			<h4>Account Usage</h4>
			<p>
				As the account holder, you are responsible for all actions taken under your account,
				including those by anyone with access to it. Please monitor and manage account
				activity to prevent misuse.
			</p>
			<p>
				If suspicious or unauthorized activity is detected, KLOOW may take steps to protect
				your account, such as temporarily suspending access or requiring additional
				verification. Our priority is to safeguard your account and personal information.
			</p>
		</div>
	</SidebarContent>
	<SidebarContent>
		<div slot="sidebar">
			<h3>Limitation of Liability</h3>
			<p>
				This section explains the limits of KLOOW’s liability in connection with the use of
				our services. Understanding these limitations helps clarify our responsibilities and
				your rights.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="basic-text">
			<h4>General Limitations</h4>
			<p>
				KLOOW is provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis. We do not guarantee that
				the service will be uninterrupted, error-free, or fully secure. We disclaim all
				warranties, whether express or implied, including but not limited to warranties of
				merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement.
			</p>
			<p>
				KLOOW is not liable for any damages resulting from the use or inability to use our
				services. This includes, but is not limited to, direct, indirect, incidental,
				special, consequential, or punitive damages, such as loss of profits, data, or other
				intangible losses.
			</p>

			<h4>Third-Party Services</h4>
			<p>
				Our platform may include integrations or links to third-party websites and services
				not owned or controlled by KLOOW. We do not endorse, guarantee, or assume
				responsibility for any third-party sites, materials, products, or services.
				Accessing or using third-party services is at your own risk.
			</p>
			<p>
				KLOOW is not liable for any loss or damage arising from interactions with
				third-party websites or services, including the sharing of your information. It is
				your responsibility to review the terms and privacy policies of any third-party
				services you choose to use.
			</p>

			<h4>Maximum Liability</h4>
			<p>
				In no event shall KLOOW’s total liability to you for all claims related to the use
				of, or inability to use, the services exceed the total amount you paid, if any, for
				accessing KLOOW during the twelve (12) months immediately preceding the claim. This
				limitation applies regardless of the type of claim, whether based on contract,
				warranty, tort, or otherwise.
			</p>
			<p>
				Some jurisdictions do not permit the exclusion or limitation of liability for
				incidental or consequential damages. In such cases, KLOOW’s liability will be
				limited to the maximum extent permitted by applicable law.
			</p>
		</div>
	</SidebarContent>
</Layout>
